When the namespace was deleted, all Persistent Volumes (PVs) stored on the NFS server were lost.
The Persistent Volume Claims (PVCs) remained but were stuck in a terminating state.
New NFS Server Setup

A new NFS server was deployed on the infra node, replacing the old one.
The new NFS setup is working correctly, and new PVs/PVCs were created and bound properly.
PVC Recreation Issue

The image registry is in managed mode, meaning the operator should automatically recreate PVCs.
However, in three namespaces, the PVCs were not recreated, causing Db2 database pods to remain in a pending state.
Other application pods relying on the database entered CrashLoopBackOff.
Db2 Cluster Instance Not Becoming Ready

During a new deployment, the Db2 cluster instance did not become ready, causing the deployment to fail.
Storage and other dependencies were checked, but the issue persisted.
Cluster-Wide Restart Attempt

Since the issue seemed related to operators not recreating storage properly, a cluster upgrade was triggered to:
Restart all cluster operators.
Restart nodes to ensure proper NFS mounts and storage reattachment.
